s & reviews","type":"newspaper-book-section","sectionId":"books","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/theguardian/guardianreview/saturdayreviewsfeatres","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/theguardian/guardianreview/saturdayreviewsfeatres","sectionName":"Books","references":[]}],"references":[]},{"webPublicationDate":"2016-02-10T15:57:41Z","webTitle":"New Harry Potter book coming out in July: the play script","sectionId":"books","type":"article","rights":{"syndicatable":"true"},"id":"books/2016/feb/10/new-harry-potter-cursed-child-eighth-book-july-play-script","fields":{"commentable":"true","byline":"Sian Cain","headline":"New Harry Potter book coming out in July: the play script","trailText":"Harry Potter and the Cursed Child Parts I &amp; II will be published the day after the play begins in London, picking up the wizard’s story 19 years after the final novel in the series","hasStoryPackage":"false","productionOffice":"UK","body":"<p>Harry Potter author JK Rowling’s script of the stage play <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/stage/2015/oct/23/harry-potter-and-the-cursed-child-west-end-london-play-sequel-youngest-son\">Harry Potter and the Cursed Child</a> is going to be published as a book moments after midnight on 31 July.</p> <p>Timed to coincide with the boy wizard’s birthday, Harry Potter and the Cursed Child Parts I and II will be published by Little, Brown in the UK and Scholastic in the US. As well as Harry’s birthday, it is also the day after the play opens in London. Pottermore, JK Rowling’s online encyclopedia for the Harry Potter universe, will simultaneously publish the ebook edition.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-tweet element--supporting\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Scholastic/status/697430195272347650\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">The eighth Harry Potter Story. Nineteen years later. Read it on July 31st! <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/CursedChild?src=hash\">#CursedChild</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/HPScriptBook?src=hash\">#HPScriptBook</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/4FNi2tltfI\">pic.twitter.com/4FNi2tltfI</a></p>&mdash; Scholastic (@Scholastic) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Scholastic/status/697430195272347650\">February 10, 2016</a></blockquote>  </figure>  <p>Rowling is working on the play with writer Jack Thorne and director John Tiffany and has said <a href=\"https://www.pottermore.com/news/cursed-child-eighth-harry-potter-story\">it is an official sequel to the original seven books</a>. It will be set 19 years after the end of the final novel, Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows, published in 2007. Harry Potter is now “an overworked employee of the Ministry of Magic, a husband and father of three school-age children”, according to a synopsis published on Pottermore last year, and the <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/stage/2015/oct/23/harry-potter-and-the-cursed-child-west-end-london-play-sequel-youngest-son\">play will focus on Harry’s youngest son, Albus Severus</a>.</p> <p>“While Harry grapples with a past that refuses to stay where it belongs, his youngest son Albus must struggle with the weight of a family legacy he never wanted. As past and present fuse ominously, both father and son learn the uncomfortable truth: sometimes, darkness comes from unexpected places,” the Pottermore synopsis describes.</p> <p>Publisher Little, Brown released JK Rowling’s first adult book, The Casual Vacancy, as well as three crime novels written under the pseudonym Robert Galbraith: The Cuckoo’s Calling, The Silkworm and Career of Evil.</p> <p>“JK Rowling and her team have received a huge number of appeals from fans who can’t be in London to see the play and who would like to read the play in book format,” said David Shelley, CEO of Little, Brown</p> <p>Literary agency The Blair Partnership, which represents Rowling, said the decision to publish the script of the play was taken following “massive public demand”.</p> <p>Split into two parts due to the “epic nature of the story” according to Rowling, those lucky enough to obtain tickets – <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/stage/2015/oct/28/booking-for-harry-potter-play-extended-due-to-high-demand\">the play sold out quickly when tickets went on sale in October</a> – can see it either on separate days or in one epic double bill. Twenty tickets for each performance will be released in an online lottery every Friday afternoon for the duration of the play’s run.</p> <p></p> <p>Bloomsbury, the UK publisher of the seven Harry Potter books, also <a href=\"http://www.mugglenet.com/2016/02/bloomsbury-reveal-plans-to-celebrate-twentieth-potter-annnivesary/\">announced plans</a> to mark the 20th anniversary of the first novel, Harry Potter and the Philosopher’s Stone in 2017, with four new editions of the book, each representing one of the houses at Hogwarts school: Gryffindor, Slytherin, Hufflepuff and Ravenclaw.</p>","liveBloggingNow":"false","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4gt8b","wordcount":"463","thumbnail":"http://media.guim.co.uk/2e3897438eaaa8993191bff872c50886a06d3101/0_117_1772_1064/140.jpg","commentCloseDate":"2016-02-17T00:00:00Z","standfirst":"<p>Harry Potter and the Cursed Child Parts I &amp; II will be published the day after the play begins in London, picking up the wizard’s story 19 years after the final novel in the series</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/feb/10/new-harry-potter-cursed-child-eighth-book-july-play-script","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/books/2016/feb/10/new-harry-potter-cursed-child-eighth-book-july-play-script","sectionName":"Books","elements":[{"id":"2e3897438eaaa8993191bff872c50886a06d3101","relation":"main","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","file":"http://media.guim.co.uk/2e3897438eaaa8993191bff872c50886a06d3101/0_117_1772_1064/1000.jpg","typeData":{"copyright":"© Debra Hurford Brown","mediaApiUri":"https://api.media.gutools.co.uk/images/2e3897438eaaa8993191bff872c50886a06d3101","altT