n criticised as sentimental and paternalistic.</p> <p>Last year saw the publication of Lee’s recently discovered manuscript, <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/books/ng-interactive/2015/jul/10/go-set-a-watchman-read-the-first-chapter\">Go Set a Watchman</a>, described as a first draft of the story that evolved into To Kill a Mockingbird. Critics and readers were startled to find the heroic Atticus disparaging black people and condemning the supreme court’s decision to outlaw segregation in public schools.</p>","liveBloggingNow":"false","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4gt2b","wordcount":"310","thumbnail":"http://media.guim.co.uk/07bea9d7b14d5aa4f6764a9feeb45e0c660af8fd/0_106_2216_1329/140.jpg","commentCloseDate":"2016-02-13T13:30:00Z","standfirst":"<p>Oscar-winning screenwriter of The Social Network working on stage version of Harper Lee’s Pulitzer-winning novel about racial prejudice </p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/stage/2016/feb/10/aaron-sorkin-to-kill-a-mockingbird-broadway-2017-2018","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/stage/2016/feb/10/aaron-sorkin-to-kill-a-mockingbird-broadway-2017-2018","sectionName":"Stage","elements":[{"id":"07bea9d7b14d5aa4f6764a9feeb45e0c660af8fd","relation":"main","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","file":"http://media.guim.co.uk/07bea9d7b14d5aa4f6764a9feeb45e0c660af8fd/0_106_2216_1329/140.jpg","typeData":{"copyright":"Copyright (c) 1962 Rex Features. No use without permission.","mediaApiUri":"https://api.media.gutools.co.uk/images/07bea9d7b14d5aa4f6764a9feeb45e0c660af8fd","suppliersReference":"840596b","altText":"Gregory Peck in the 1962 film version of To Kill A Mockingbird.","caption":"Adaptable character … Gregory Peck as Atticus Finch in the 1962 film version of To Kill A Mockingbird.","photographer":"Everett/REX Shutterstock","source":"Everett/REX Shutterstock","credit":"Photograph: Everett/REX Shutterstock","mediaId":"07bea9d7b14d5aa4f6764a9feeb45e0c660af8fd","displayCredit":"true","imageType":"Photograph","s